properties.location: the King River at Docker Road
properties.webBody:
This Minor Flood Warning is being issued for the King River at Docker Road.

MINOR FLOODING POSSIBLE AT DOCKER RD BRIDGE OVERNIGHT MONDAY

In the 24 hours to 9 am Monday, rainfall totals of 5 - 20 mm have been recorded in the King River catchment.

Since 9 am Monday, additional rainfall totals of up to 20 mm have been recorded. River levels are elevated along the King River in response to the rainfall. 

A minor flood peak is possible at Docker Rd Bridge overnight Monday into Tuesday.

No significant rainfall is forecast for the remainder of Monday and into Tuesday.

King River:
Minor flooding may occur along the King River. 

The King River at Docker Rd Bridge is currently at 2.86 metres and rising, below the minor flood level. 

The King River at Docker Rd Bridge may peak around the minor flood level (3.70 metres) overnight Monday into Tuesday.
Stay informed - monitor your local conditions and remain alert.
What you should do: 

  • Be prepared to act if your situation changes.
  • You should stay informed by listening to emergency broadcasters and monitoring warnings.
  • Farmers should consider moving livestock and machinery to higher ground.
  • Floodwater is dangerous - never drive, walk or ride through floodwater.
  • Monitor weather forecasts and river levels. Go to www.bom.gov.au/vic/warnings/
Impacts in your area: 

  • High river levels and potential flooding in areas close to rivers and streams.
  • Low lying caravan parks and camping grounds may be flooded.
  • Local roads may be closed and low bridges may be underwater.
This message was issued by State Emergency Service.

The next update is expected by 20/06/2023 01:00 pm or as the situation changes.

Use multiple sources to stay informed:
  • www.emergency.vic.gov.au
  • VicEmergency Hotline - freecall 1800 226 226
  • VicEmergency app
  • Facebook or Twitter (#vicfloods)
  • Tune in to ABC Local Radio, commercial and designated community radio stations, or Sky News TV.

Accessibility: 
The following services can help you, or someone you know, access information during an emergency. 
  • To access this information in other languages call the Translating and Interpreting Service on 131 450 (freecall) and ask them to call VicEmergency Hotline. 
  • If you are deaf, hard of hearing, or have a speech/communication impairment contact National Relay Service on 1800 555 677 and ask them to call the VicEmergency Hotline.

properties.webBody:
This Minor Flood Warning is being issued for the Sevens & Castle Creeks at Euroa.

MINOR FLOODING LIKELY AT EUROA MONDAY EVENING

In the 24 hours to 9 am Monday, rainfall totals of 10 - 20 mm have been recorded in the Seven and Castle Creeks catchment. Since 9 am Monday, additional totals of up to 15 mm have been recorded. 

River levels are elevated in response to the rainfall including at Strathbogie, where river levels are approaching the minor flood level. A minor flood peak is likely at Euroa overnight Monday into Tuesday.

No significant rainfall is forecast for the remainder of Monday and into Tuesday.

Castle Creek:
River levels are elevated on Castle Creek at Telfords Bridge though are below the minor flood level.

Seven Creeks to Euroa:
Minor flooding is likely along the Seven Creeks to Euroa.

The Seven Creeks at Euroa is currently at 2.02 metres and rising, below the minor flood level.
 
The Seven Creeks at Euroa is likely to exceed the minor flood level (2.50 m) Monday evening. The river level may peak near 2.70 metres overnight Monday into Tuesday.
Stay informed - monitor your local conditions and remain alert.
What you should do: 

  • Be prepared to act if your situation changes.
  • You should stay informed by listening to emergency broadcasters and monitoring warnings.
  • Farmers should consider moving livestock and machinery to higher ground.
  • Floodwater is toxic - never play or swim in floodwater.
  • Monitor weather forecasts and river levels. Go to www.bom.gov.au/vic/warnings/
Impacts in your area: 

  • High river levels and potential flooding in areas close to rivers and streams.
  • Local flooding in streets and along overland flow paths is likely if there is local rain
  • The Caravan Park, Rotary Park, land opposite the Memorial Oval and the Bowls Club may begin to be inundated
This message was issued by State Emergency Service.

The next update is expected by 20/06/2023 11:00 am or as the situation changes.

  • VicEmergency Hotline - freecall 1800 226 226
